Transcriptome comparison script

library(data.table)
library(stringr)
library(ggplot2)
library(IRanges)
library(GenomicRanges)
paf_names_vector<-c("rnaspades_day1_to_nohic_Esu.paf","rnaspades_day10_to_nohic_Esu.paf","rnaspades_together_to_nohic_Esu.paf", "rnaspades_single_lib_to_nohic_Esu.paf","Trinityd1transOnEunapius.paf","Trinityd10transOnEunapius.paf","trinity_day1_10_qual_to_nohic_Esu.paf")

compare_transcriptomes<-function(paf_names_vector,wd=getwd()) {
  
  setwd(wd)
#Importing paf format transcriptomes to pre-HiC genome mappings

table_list<-lapply(1:length(paf_names_vector),function(x) {
  fread(paf_names_vector[x],fill=T)[,1:12] %>% 
  setnames(.,c("query_name","query_length","query_start","query_end","strand","target_name","target_length","target_start","target_end","matches","alignment_block","mapping_quality")) 
})
transcriptome_names<-str_extract(paf_names_vector,".*(?=.paf)")

#Filtering for multiple mappings of the same transcript, taking only the mappings with maximum matches for every transcript
#this may be unoptimal so we'll filter the alignments to retain only primary mappings
#we'll analyse significant secondary mappings as well - which genes are that? secondary sites probably represent duplications or pseudogenes - maybe we can detect larger areas of duplication in this way

table_list<-lapply(1:length(table_list),function(x) {
  table_list[[x]]<-table_list[[x]][mapping_quality>0]
})

#Adding transcript names without isoforms: (literatura kaze da bih trebao ostaviti TRINITY_blabla_cX_gY, da to predstavlja jedan gen. Ipak, pogledao sam na jako puno mjesta, svi ti g_Y se overlapaju, tako da sam kao imena gena ostavljao TRINITY_blabla_cX)

table_list<-lapply(1:length(table_list),function(x) {
    if(grepl("NODE",table_list[[x]]$query_name[1])==T) {
  table_list[[x]][,transcript_name_no_iso:=str_extract( table_list[[x]]$query_name,"g\\d+")] 
  }
  else if(grepl("TRINITY",table_list[[x]]$query_name[1])==T) {
    table_list[[x]][,transcript_name_no_iso:=str_extract( table_list[[x]]$query_name,".*(?=_g\\d+_i\\d+)")] 
  }
})

#Making GRanges objects

granges_list<-lapply(1:length(table_list), function(x) {
makeGRangesFromDataFrame(df=table_list[[x]],seqnames.field = "target_name",start.field = "target_start",end.field = "target_end",strand.field = "strand",keep.extra.columns = T)
})

#Splitting the IRanges into "genes" (razdvajam po genima - trenutno nas ne zanimaju overlapovi izmedu tranksripata koji medusobno ne pripadaju istim genima)

split_list<-lapply(1:length(granges_list),function(x) {
  split(granges_list[[x]],granges_list[[x]]$transcript_name_no_iso)
})

#Reducing transcripts into genes (ignore.strand=T zbog toga sto RNAseq knjiznica nije strand dependent)
genes_list<-c()

for(i in 1:length(split_list)) {
  genes_list<-c(genes_list,unlist(reduce(split_list[[i]],ignore.strand=T)))
  genes_list[[i]]$gene<-names(genes_list[[i]])
  i<-i+1
}


#Multiple locations - different genes (buduci da se izoforme pojedinih transkripata mapiraju na vise ne preklapajucih mjesta, neke cak i na druge kontige, svim takvim skupinama izoformi sam dao razlicita imena gena (svaka skupina izoformi mapirana na razlicito mjesto - novi naziv gena))


genes_diff_loc<-lapply(1:length(genes_list), function(x) {
genes_dt<-as.data.table(genes_list[[x]])
genes_dt[,gene_group_number:=rleid(.SD$start),by=gene]
genes_dt[,gene_more:=ifelse(length(unique(.SD$start))==1,T,F),by=gene]
genes_dt[,gene_group:=paste(gene,gene_group_number,sep="_")]
genes_dt[gene_more==F,gene:=gene_group]
genes_mult<-makeGRangesFromDataFrame(genes_dt,keep.extra.columns = T) 
return(genes_mult)
})

#Multiple locations - different contigs - gene counts (vizualizacija broja gena cije se izoforme mapiraju na razlicita mjesta u genomu)

genes_diff_counts<-lapply(1:length(genes_list),function(x) {
  genes_dt<-as.data.table(genes_list[[x]])
  genes_dt[,gene_same_loc:=ifelse(uniqueN(start)==1,T,F),by=gene]
  genes_dt[,gene_more_same_con:=ifelse(uniqueN(start)!=1 & uniqueN(seqnames)==1,T,F),by=gene]
  genes_dt[,gene_more_diff_con:=ifelse(uniqueN(seqnames)==1,T,F),by=gene]
  counts<-c(nrow(genes_dt[gene_same_loc==T]),nrow(genes_dt[gene_more_same_con==T]),nrow(genes_dt[gene_more_diff_con==F]))
  transcriptome<-rep(transcriptome_names[x],3)
  location<-c("same position","different position, same contig", "different contig")
  location_dt<-data.table(transcriptomes=transcriptome,gene_counts=counts,location=location)
  return(location_dt)
})


plot_table_location<-rbindlist(genes_diff_counts)
location_plot<-ggplot(data=plot_table_location,aes(x=transcriptomes,y=gene_counts,fill=location)) +
         geom_bar(position="fill",stat = "identity", width=0.45) +
  theme_bw() +
   theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 50, hjust = 1,size=7.5))  +
  labs(x="Trancriptome",y="Proportion of genes") +
theme(legend.position="top") +
   theme(legend.title=element_blank()) +
     ggtitle("Number of genes whose isoforms map on different locations") +
   theme(plot.title = element_text(size=10))


#Mapped isoform counting (brojanje izoformi na temelju preklapanja gena i tranksripata, pazim da uzmem samo preklapanja izmedu gena i tranksripata iz te skupine gena) + vizualizacija distribucije broja izoformi

isoforms<-lapply(1:length(genes_list),function(x) {
  overlaps_gene_trans<-findOverlaps(genes_list[[x]],granges_list[[x]])
overlaps_gene_trans_table<-cbind(as.data.table(genes_list[[x]][queryHits(overlaps_gene_trans)]),as.data.table(granges_list[[x]][subjectHits(overlaps_gene_trans)]))
overlaps_gene_trans_table<-overlaps_gene_trans_table[gene==transcript_name_no_iso]
transcriptome_isoforms<-overlaps_gene_trans_table[,.N,by=gene][order(-N)]
counts_vector<-transcriptome_isoforms$N
transcriptomes_vector<-rep(transcriptome_names[x],length(transcriptome_isoforms$N))
 isoform_plot_table<-data.table(isoform_counts=counts_vector,transcriptome=transcriptomes_vector)
  return(isoform_plot_table)
})
isoform_counts_table<-rbindlist(isoforms)
plot_isoforms_sameloc<-ggplot(data=isoform_counts_table,aes(x=isoform_counts,fill=transcriptome)) +
  geom_density()+
  coord_cartesian(xlim=c(1,15)) +
  facet_wrap(.~transcriptome) +
  labs(x="Number of isoforms") +
    theme_bw() +
  theme(axis.title.y=element_blank()) +
   ggtitle("Distribution of mapped isoform numbers in all transcriptomes (isoforms on different locations - same genes) (1-15) ") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size=9)) +
  theme(legend.position="none") 

plot_isoforms_sameloc_scaled<-ggplot(data=isoform_counts_table,aes(x=isoform_counts,y=..scaled..,fill=transcriptome)) +
  geom_density()+
  coord_cartesian(xlim=c(1,15)) +
  facet_wrap(.~transcriptome) +
  labs(x="Number of isoforms") +
    theme_bw() +
  theme(axis.title.y=element_blank()) +
   ggtitle("Distribution of mapped isoform numbers in all transcriptomes (isoforms on different locations - same genes) (1-15) (scaled)") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size=7.5)) +
  theme(legend.position="none")

#Mapped isoform counting (ponovno brojanje izoformi, drugaciji rezultat ako kao gene uzmemo skupove izoformi na razlicitim mjestima u genomu)

isoforms<-lapply(1:length(genes_diff_loc),function(x) {
  overlaps_gene_trans<-findOverlaps(genes_diff_loc[[x]],granges_list[[x]])
overlaps_gene_trans_table<-cbind(as.data.table(genes_diff_loc[[x]][queryHits(overlaps_gene_trans)]),as.data.table(granges_list[[x]][subjectHits(overlaps_gene_trans)]))
overlaps_gene_trans_table<-overlaps_gene_trans_table[gene==transcript_name_no_iso]
transcriptome_isoforms<-overlaps_gene_trans_table[,.N,by=gene][order(-N)]
counts_vector<-transcriptome_isoforms$N
transcriptomes_vector<-rep(transcriptome_names[x],length(transcriptome_isoforms$N))
 isoform_plot_table<-data.table(isoform_counts=counts_vector,transcriptome=transcriptomes_vector)
  return(isoform_plot_table)
})


isoform_counts_table<-rbindlist(isoforms)


plot_isoforms_diffloc<-ggplot(data=isoform_counts_table,aes(x=isoform_counts,fill=transcriptome)) +
  geom_density()+
  coord_cartesian(xlim=c(1,15)) +
  facet_wrap(.~transcriptome) +
  labs(x="Number of isoforms") +
    theme_bw() +
  theme(axis.title.y=element_blank()) +
   ggtitle("Distribution of mapped isoform numbers in all transcriptomes (isoforms on different locations - different genes) (1-15)") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size=9)) +
  theme(legend.position="none") 


plot_isoforms_diffloc_scaled<-ggplot(data=isoform_counts_table,aes(x=isoform_counts,y=..scaled..,fill=transcriptome)) +
  geom_density()+
  coord_cartesian(xlim=c(1,15)) +
  facet_wrap(.~transcriptome) +
  labs(x="Number of isoforms") +
    theme_bw() +
  theme(axis.title.y=element_blank()) +
   ggtitle("Distribution of mapped isoform numbers in all transcriptomes (isoforms on different locations - different genes) (1-15) (scaled)") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size=7.5)) +
  theme(legend.position="none") 

#Gene length histograms

lengths_table<-lapply(1:length(genes_diff_loc), function(x) {
  widths<-width(genes_diff_loc[[x]])
 transcriptomes_vector<-rep(transcriptome_names[x],length(widths))
 lengths_table<-data.table(transcriptomes=transcriptomes_vector,lengths=widths)
}) 
lengths_table_plot<-rbindlist(lengths_table)

plot_lengths<-ggplot(data=lengths_table_plot,aes(x=lengths,fill=transcriptomes)) +
  geom_density()  +
  coord_cartesian(xlim=c(0,15000))+
  facet_wrap(.~transcriptomes) +
 labs(x="Gene length") +
    theme_bw() +
  theme(axis.title.y=element_blank()) +
   ggtitle("Distribution of gene lengths in all transcriptomes (0-15000)") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size=11)) +
  theme(legend.position="none") 


plot_lengths_scaled<-ggplot(data=lengths_table_plot,aes(x=lengths,y=..scaled..,fill=transcriptomes)) +
  geom_density()  +
  coord_cartesian(xlim=c(0,15000))+
  facet_wrap(.~transcriptomes) +
 labs(x="Gene length") +
    theme_bw() +
  theme(axis.title.y=element_blank()) +
   ggtitle("Distribution of gene lengths in all transcriptomes (0-15000) (scaled)") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size=11)) +
  theme(legend.position="none") 

#Gene counts

lengths_table_plot[,more_than_2000:=ifelse(lengths>=2000,T,F)]
more_than_2000_counts<-lengths_table_plot[,sum(more_than_2000),by=transcriptomes]
less_than_2000_counts<-lengths_table_plot[,nrow(.SD)-sum(more_than_2000),by=transcriptomes]
gene_counts<-data.table(transcriptome=rep(unique(lengths_table_plot$transcriptomes),2),length=c(rep("more than 2000 bp",length(paf_names_vector)),rep("less than 2000 bp",length(paf_names_vector ))),counts=c(more_than_2000_counts$V1,less_than_2000_counts$V1))
plot_gene_numb<-ggplot(data=gene_counts,aes(x=reorder(transcriptome,-counts),y=counts,fill=length)) +
         geom_bar(position="stack",stat = "identity", width=0.65) +
  theme_bw() +
   theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1,size=7.5)) +
  labs(x="Trancriptome",y="Number of genes") +
theme(legend.position="top") +
   theme(legend.title=element_blank()) +
     ggtitle("Number of genes with marked length") +
   theme(plot.title = element_text(size=10))

plot_gene_prop<-ggplot(data=gene_counts,aes(x=reorder(transcriptome,-counts),y=counts,fill=length)) +
         geom_bar(position="fill",stat = "identity", width=0.5) +
  theme_bw() +
   theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1,size=7.5)) +
  labs(x="Trancriptome",y="Proportion of genes") +
theme(legend.position="top") +
   theme(legend.title=element_blank()) +
     ggtitle("Proportion of genes with marked length") +
   theme(plot.title = element_text(size=11))

#Gene coverage (by transcripts)
coverages<-lapply(1:length(genes_diff_loc),function(x) {
  overlaps_gene_trans<-findOverlaps(genes_diff_loc[[x]],granges_list[[x]])
overlaps_gene_trans_table<-cbind(as.data.table(genes_diff_loc[[x]][queryHits(overlaps_gene_trans)]),as.data.table(granges_list[[x]][subjectHits(overlaps_gene_trans)]))
overlaps_gene_trans_table<-overlaps_gene_trans_table[gene==transcript_name_no_iso]
setnames(overlaps_gene_trans_table,c("seqnames_1","start_1","end_1","width_1","strand_1","gene_1","gene_group_number_1","gene_more_1","gene_group_1","seqnames_2","start_2","end_2","width_2","strand_2","query_name","query_length","query_start","query_end","target_length","matches","alignment_block","mapping_quality","transcript_name_no_iso"))
overlaps_gene_trans_table[,start_on_gene:=start_2-start_1]
overlaps_gene_trans_table[,end_on_gene:=width_2+start_on_gene-1]
gr_cov<-makeGRangesFromDataFrame(overlaps_gene_trans_table,seqnames.field = "gene_1",start.field = "start_on_gene",end.field = "end_on_gene",ignore.strand = T,keep.extra.columns = T )
mean_covs<-mean(coverage(gr_cov))
cov_dt<-data.table(mean_coverage=mean_covs,transcriptome=rep(transcriptome_names[x],length(mean_covs)))
return(cov_dt)
})

coverages_dt<-rbindlist(coverages)

plot_coverage<-ggplot(data=coverages_dt,aes(x=mean_coverage,fill=transcriptome)) +
  geom_density() +
  facet_wrap(.~transcriptome) +
  coord_cartesian(xlim=c(1,5)) +
  theme_bw() +
  xlab("mean(coverage)")+
  theme(axis.title.y=element_blank()) +
  theme(legend.position="none") +
  ggtitle("Mean coverage distribution for every gene") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size=11))


plot_coverage_scaled<-ggplot(data=coverages_dt,aes(x=mean_coverage,y=..scaled..,fill=transcriptome)) +
  geom_density() +
  facet_wrap(.~transcriptome) +
  coord_cartesian(xlim=c(1,5)) +
  theme_bw() +
  xlab("mean(coverage)")+
  theme(axis.title.y=element_blank()) +
  theme(legend.position="none") +
  ggtitle("Mean coverage distribution for every gene (scaled)") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size=11))

plot_list<-list(location_plot,plot_isoforms_sameloc,plot_isoforms_sameloc_scaled,plot_isoforms_diffloc,plot_isoforms_diffloc_scaled,plot_lengths,plot_lengths_scaled,plot_gene_numb,plot_gene_prop,plot_coverage,plot_coverage_scaled)
return(plot_list)
}
plot_list<-compare_transcriptomes(paf_names_vector,wd ="C:/Users/User/Desktop")
plot_list
